duced into Britain by the Normans; it has since remained in continuous use. It is derived from the nearly synonymous elements <i>hrōd</i> ‘fame’ + <i>berht</i> ‘bright, famous’, and had a native Old English predecessor of similar form (<i>Hreodbeorht</i>), which was supplanted by the Norman name. Two dukes of Normandy in the 11th century bore the name: the father of  William the Conqueror  (sometimes identified with the legendary Robert the Devil), and his eldest son. It was borne also by three kings of Scotland, notably  Robert the Bruce  (  1274–1329 ), who freed Scotland from English domination. The altered short form <i>Bob</i> is very common, but <i>Hob</i> and <i>Dob</i>, which were common in the Middle Ages and gave rise to surnames, are extinct.  See also  Rupert ."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"Mrs. Robert Malet was born in 1085, in Enmore, Somerset, England, United Kingdom. She had at least 1 son with Robert Malet II Of Curry."},"et":{"1085–":"1085–Surnud","1080–Male":"1080–Surnud","1115–Male":"1115–Surnud","1085–Female":"1085–Surnud","1080":"1080","1115":"1115","1085":"1085","Enmore, Somerset, England, United Kingdom":"Enmore, Somerset, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"1085–":"1085–Kuollut","1080–Male":"1080–Kuollut","1115–Male":"1115–Kuollut","1085–Female":"1085–Kuollut","1080":"1080","1115":"1115","1085":"1085","Enmore, Somerset, England, United Kingdom":"Enmore, Somerset, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta"},"fr":{"1085–":"1085–Décédée","1080–Male":"1080–Décédé","1115–Male":"1115–Décédé","1085–Female":"1085–Décédée","1080":"1080","1115":"1115","1085":"1085","Enmore, Somerset, England, United Kingdom":"Enmore, Somerset, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","lifeSummary":"Mrs. Robert Malet est née en 1085, à Enmore, Somerset, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni. Elle a eu au moins 1 fils avec Robert Malet II Of Curry."},"de":{"1085–":"1085–Verstorben","1080–Male":"1080–Verstorben","1115–Male":"1115–Verstorben","1085–Female":"1085–Verstorben","1080":"1080","1115":"1115","108